HEADWORD: Sandnecker
<hw>Sand"neck`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A European flounder (<spn>Hippoglossoides limandoides</spn>); --
called also <altname>rough dab</altname>, <altname>long fluke</altname>,
<altname>sand fluke</altname>, and <altname>sand
sucker</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

